50|$|<b>Hooded</b> <b>wheatear</b> {{feeds on}} insects, often {{taken in the}} air. Its call is a whistled vit, and the song is a harsh chattering.|$|E
50|$|In {{summer the}} male <b>hooded</b> <b>wheatear</b> {{is a white}} and black bird. The white crown and belly {{contrast}} with the black face, back and throat. The tail and rump are white with black central tail feathers.|$|E
